\sqrt{7} &= \frac{1}{8}\left[\frac{2}{3}\sqrt{9} + \frac{1}{21}(256)^{3/4}\sqrt{9}\right] + \frac{C}{8} \\
\Rightarrow C &= 8\sqrt{7} - \frac{2}{3}\sqrt{9} - \frac{1}{21}(256)^{3/4}\sqrt{9}
\end{align*}
Finally, we can evaluate $y(256)$ using the formula we derived earlier:
\begin{align*}
